### Styling
- Use NativeWind classes (NOT inline styles)
- Example: `className="bg-dark-bg text-dark-fg"`
- Opacity: `className="text-dark-fg/60"` (60% opacity)

## Adding Reusables Components

DO NOT build components from scratch. Use React Native Reusables:

```bash
cd packages/design-system
npx @react-native-reusables/cli add button
```

This creates `src/components/ui/button.tsx` which automatically uses Dark branding (configured in `tailwind.config.js`).

## When to Use Squircles

Only wrap Reusables components in Squircle if they need smooth corners:

```tsx
// If Reusables Button uses rounded corners
import { Button as ReusablesButton } from './ui/button';
import { Squircle } from '../squircle/squircle-view';

// Create a wrapped version
export function SquircleButton({ children, ...props }) {
  return (
    <Squircle cornerSmoothing={0.6}>
      <ReusablesButton {...props}>{children}</ReusablesButton>
    </Squircle>
  );
}
```

## Custom Components (Rare)

Only create custom components for things NOT in Reusables (e.g., FAB).

See `src/components/custom/fab.tsx` as an example.

## Exports
Always export from `src/index.ts`:
```ts
export { Button } from './components/ui/button';
export { FAB } from './components/custom/fab';
```
